    <p>Need an instant answer? Open the <a href="https://mycalcstool.com/en/percentage-calculator"><strong>Percentage Calculator</strong></a> and use the percentage change mode.</p>
  </blockquote>

  <hr />

  <h2>FAQ</h2>

  <h3>How do I calculate percentage increase quickly?</h3>
  <p>Subtract the old value from the new value, divide by the old value, then multiply by 100.</p>

  <h3>What is the formula for percentage increase?</h3>
  <p><strong>((New Value - Original Value) / Original Value) x 100</strong></p>

  <h3>Is percentage increase the same as percentage change?</h3>
  <p>No. Percentage increase applies only when the value goes up. Percentage change can describe either an increase or a decrease.</p>

  <h3>Can percentage increase be more than 100%?</h3>
  <p>Yes. If a value more than doubles, the increase is greater than 100%.</p>
  <p>Example: from 50 to 125 gives a <strong>150% increase</strong>.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Final Takeaway</h2>
  <p>Percentage increase is easy once you remember one rule: <strong>always divide by the original number</strong>.</p>
  <p>That one step prevents most mistakes in budgeting, reporting, pricing, and school math.</p>
  <p>If you want to skip the manual math, use the free <a href="https://mycalcstool.com/en/percentage-calculator"><strong>Percentage Calculator</strong></a> to get the answer instantly.</p>
